Introduction
As a newly selected Student Digital Ambassador, my role is to help peers navigate the digital world safely and professionally. This project involved building a comprehensive Digital Literacy Portfolio hosted on GitHub. The objective was to complete five tasks covering essential digital modules, ranging from professional identity and coding collaboration to email etiquette and cybercrime awareness. This report documents my work, reflections, and the digital tools utilized to fulfill this mandate.
________________________________________
Task 1 Write-up: Digital Literacy Awareness Infographic
•	Tool Used: Canva 
•	Content: I created a visual resource covering three topics: digital tools for students, safe internet practices, and professional online presence.
•	Reflection: I used Canva to design a one-page visual that simplifies complex digital literacy concepts for my batchmates. The infographic highlights the importance of protecting one’s digital footprint and using productivity tools effectively. One interesting aspect was learning how to use visual hierarchy to make safety tips more engaging. The most difficult part was condensing the information to ensure the design remained clean and professional while still being informative.
________________________________________
Task 2 Write-up: Build Your Student Digital Portfolio
•	Platforms Set Up: GitHub, LinkedIn, and Kaggle.
•	Reflection: I established my foundational professional presence on GitHub, LinkedIn, and Kaggle. On LinkedIn, I updated my education section with my current degree and institution. On GitHub, I created a profile README with my branch and learning goals. LinkedIn will serve as my primary networking tool, while GitHub and Kaggle will host my technical projects. Over the next four years, I plan to use these platforms to showcase my skill progression to potential internship coordinators and the academic community.
________________________________________
Task 3 Write-up: Explore Coding & Collaboration Platforms
•	Platforms Used: HackerRank and Google Forms.
•	Deliverable Link: Digital Literacy Awareness Quiz
•	Reflection: For the coding portion, I used HackerRank to complete a beginner-level challenge to familiarize myself with competitive programming environments. For collaboration, I built a 'Digital Literacy Awareness Quiz' using Google Forms with exactly five questions. These tools are academically essential as they allow me to practice problem-solving and manage data through cloud-based collaboration. This Google Form can now be used as a real tool to gauge the digital literacy of my batchmates in my role as an ambassador.
________________________________________
Task 4 Write-up: Draft a Professional Email & Etiquette Guide
•	Reflection: This task focused on professional online communication, which is a core responsibility of a Digital Ambassador. I drafted two professional emails—one requesting an assignment extension and another inquiring about an internship opportunity—ensuring proper subject lines, greetings, and structure. I also developed a 5-point 'Do’s and Don’ts' checklist for social media use. A key learning is that poor digital communication can lead to professional misunderstandings. For example, a poorly structured email to a professor might result in a rejected request simply due to a lack of clarity and professional tone.
________________________________________
Task 5 Write-up: Cybercrime Awareness Case Study & Prevention
•	Case Study Topic: Phishing.
•	Reflection: Researching phishing revealed how sophisticated deceptive emails have become in targeting students. What surprised me most was the step-by-step psychological manipulation used to trick victims into clicking malicious links. As a result, I have changed my personal habit of clicking links from unknown senders without first verifying the source. I also integrated the National Cyber Crime Portal (cybercrime.gov.in) and the 1930 Helpline into my prevention checklist to ensure my peers have immediate access to reporting channels.
________________________________________
Conclusion
This project has successfully established my professional digital framework. Through the five modules, I have moved from basic awareness to practical application in coding, professional networking, and cybersecurity. As a Student Digital Ambassador, I now possess the tools and the repository necessary to guide my peers toward safe and responsible digital citizenship.
